'''Garrick Hagon''' is a British-born, Canadian actor who portrayed [[Biggs Darklighter]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']]. He was raised in Toronto, Canada and is a stage, television, and film actor.

He is also well known to sci-fi fans as Ky in the [[Wikipedia:Doctor Who|Doctor Who]] storyline [[Wikipedia:The Mutants|The Mutants]] (1972). He reappeared in ''Doctor Who'' in 2012, as Abraham in the episode "A Town Called Mercy".

Hagon's voice-over credits include the radio drama ''Judge Dredd: Jihad'', as a psychotic clone of [[Toby Longworth]]'s Joseph Dredd; the 1996 Manga Video dub of ''Lupin III: The Mystery of Mamo'' and ''Lupin III: Bye Bye Liberty Crisis'' as Goemon Ishikawa XIII; and the 2015 video game ''Batman: Arkham Knight'', as a clone of the Joker (voiced by fellow ''Star Wars'' alumnus [[Mark Hamill]]).

